Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

This page gives you guidance on how to stay safely in Turkmenistan as a visitor, if you are unable to return to the UK.
Everyone should comply with the measures put in place in Turkmenistan to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
Moving around in Turkmenistan
There are restrictions on road travel within Turkmenistan. All road borders are closed. The International Seaport of Turkmenistan at Turkmenbashi is closed to passenger traffic. Traffic police check points have been established around major population centres, including Ashgabat, and road users may be subject to temperature screening.
Internal air and rail passengers may also be subject to temperature checks.
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy on +993 12 36 34 62/64.
